<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS, RINGS AND SLEEVES - PISTON AND ROD
        ASSEMBLY - CONNECTING ROD BEARING INSERTS &#38; CAPS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CONNECTING ROD BEARING INSERTS &#38; CAPS</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="e415_115.xml" xrefid="hl4150605">"BEARING FITTING PROCEDURE"</hotlnk>
                    earlier in this section for running and side clearance procedures.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the bearing inserts lubricated, install the connecting rod cap so the numbers on the
                cap and rod match. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150661">6.61</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the bolts by hand into the rods fingertight. Tighten the bolts to the specified
                torque. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150662">6.62</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check connecting rod side clearance (See
                <hotlnk document="e415_HL4150601.xml" xrefid="hl4150601">"SPECIFICATIONS"</hotlnk>) Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e415_115.xml" xrefid="ef4150640">6.40</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <para>Reinstall the following components. Refer to the appropriate manual section for installation
                procedures.
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Pick-up tube</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Pan</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Vibration damper and pulley</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Cylinder head assembly (with intake manifold, exhaust manifold, thermostat housing and
                        turbocharger attached)
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Rocker arm assembly</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Turbocharger oil inlet and drain tubes</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Thermostat housing to water pump hose</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>
                        <hotlnk document="e415_HL4150407.xml" xrefid="hl4150406">ADJUST VALVE LASH.</hotlnk>
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Valve cover and new gasket</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Aneroid tube</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Fuel leak-off lines (low pressure)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Fuel injection lines (high pressure)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Crossover pipe</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Crankcase breather tube</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <figure id="ef4150661" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11573" filename="../figcg1/CG11573.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.61. Install Connecting Rod Cap and Bearing.</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4150662" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11574" filename="../figcg1/CG11574.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.62. Tighten Connecting Rod Nuts.</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
